<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="a2Apr1939"><font color="red">2 April 1939</font> <i>NLFF</i> (from Paul L&eacute;on to Richard de la Mere): I have shown the jacket to Mr Joyce and I only hope that it is not definite yet. (1) The front and back of it as they stand now could not possibly do. As printed in the same characters the title and the name of the author make a sentence which will be the standing joke everywhere and the addition of the word &ldquo;by&rdquo; is thus made absolutely necessary &hellip; (2) The back also being printed in equal characters does not look beautiful and should be changed in the same idea. </div>
